<div id="review_1639513509" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1639513509" />
    <a title="Bobbie Stanley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50969628-bobbie-stanley"><img alt="Bobbie Stanley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1451785966p2/50969628.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1639513509?book_show_action=true">May 16, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bobbie Stanley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bobbie Stanley" href="/user/show/50969628-bobbie-stanley">Bobbie Stanley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1639513509" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11321530615660326469">I am SO EXCITED to share this book with you guys! It literally sucked me in from the moment I started it and I couldn&apos;t put it down. Like almost didn&apos;t sleep for a day or two because that would mean I&apos;d have to stop reading for a few hours and I needed to know what was going to happen! The concept of this novel is incredibly creative. I love the way they use the watches to keep the time on their lives. It&apos;s something I haven&apos;t seen done before, but something that I could totally see happening wi</span>
  <span id="freeText11321530615660326469" style="display:none">I am SO EXCITED to share this book with you guys! It literally sucked me in from the moment I started it and I couldn't put it down. Like almost didn't sleep for a day or two because that would mean I'd have to stop reading for a few hours and I needed to know what was going to happen! The concept of this novel is incredibly creative. I love the way they use the watches to keep the time on their lives. It's something I haven't seen done before, but something that I could totally see happening with the way that our world uses technology. The world in this novel has just taken it a step further. I almost feel like this is a historical time period, which his funny considering the extent of the use of technology. It's really well done and the setting and characters are very well crafted. You can feel every moment with these characters. <br /><br />It would be so easy for things to happen too quickly given the pace of the action in this story. There is a lot of adventure and a lot of things need to happen in a rather small time space. Even so, the author remains true to human nature and allows relationships and growth between and within characters to occur at a natural and believable pace. It's been a while since I've read something where I enjoyed the growth of characters so immensely. <br /><br />Between the action, the creativity, and the fact that the characters were so easy to connect with, it was pretty much a given that this book would be good. As if that wasn't enough, though, the author also tackled some really excellent ethical questions. I loved the exploration of how much involvement in our own time and mortality is too much and whether people really ought to know how much time they have left in their lives. Technically, this isn't a dystopian novel. It does, however, raise questions in much the same manner, and it leaves the reader with a lot to think about. I absolutely loved reading it and I really would like more of this world, either with the same characters or with others. I would love to see this as part of a series. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11321530615660326469" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


