<div id="review_1671785228" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1671785228" />
    <a title="Jessica" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49801670-jessica"><img alt="Jessica" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1671785228?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jessica" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jessica" href="/user/show/49801670-jessica">Jessica</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1671785228" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1896667617225673378">27 Days to Midnight is fantastic - I highly recommend it to anyone who likes adventure novels, particularly fun, fast-paced, exciting adventure novels. And since I don&apos;t think anyone likes novels that are un-fun, slow, and boring...well, I guess I&apos;d recommend it to anyone.<br/><br/>In all seriousness, there were several elements that worked together to make this one of the best debut novels I&apos;ve read. To start, the pacing was phenomenal. The book was exciting and tightly paced, but there was enough detail</span>
  <span id="freeText1896667617225673378" style="display:none">27 Days to Midnight is fantastic - I highly recommend it to anyone who likes adventure novels, particularly fun, fast-paced, exciting adventure novels. And since I don't think anyone likes novels that are un-fun, slow, and boring...well, I guess I'd recommend it to anyone.<br /><br />In all seriousness, there were several elements that worked together to make this one of the best debut novels I've read. To start, the pacing was phenomenal. The book was exciting and tightly paced, but there was enough detail included for the reader to feel like he/she was truly a part of the story. There was never any confusion about background that was glossed over superficially, but at the same time, the book was never, ever dull. Second, the character development was exceptional, especially for a YA group. Both Dahlia and Farren are dynamic characters that the reader can fall in love with and root for - and that's not even getting into the side characters or the villain, all of whom have interesting back stories and vibrant personalities.<br /><br />Finally, amidst all the action (and there is LOT of that!), the book touches on mature themes that lend credibility and meaning to the story. A world where everyone knows exactly when they are going to die is fascinating, and Kristine Kruppa manages to touch lightly on some of these intricacies in a way that is both intriguing and thought-provoking.<br /><br />Overall, well done - if you're a reader, you should read this book. And if you're the author...please write some more stuff!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1896667617225673378" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


