<div id="review_1711109168" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1711109168" />
    <a title="Crystal Qualkenbush" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58128267-crystal-qualkenbush"><img alt="Crystal Qualkenbush" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1602685194p2/58128267.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1711109168?book_show_action=true">Jul 27, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Crystal Qualkenbush" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Crystal Qualkenbush" href="/user/show/58128267-crystal-qualkenbush">Crystal Qualkenbush</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1711109168" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4343953362480335185">I loved this book! I can honestly say I had never read a Steampunk novel before, however, I am interested in Steampunk as a concept so this book was a fascinating thought to me. I appreciated the depth behind each character. Everyone had a back story, and &quot;skeletons in their closet&quot; so to speak, that gave them the little nuances that built them into very intriguing characters. I could feel myself sympathizing with the entire cast of characters; not just the protagonists, but the villain as well.</span>
  <span id="freeText4343953362480335185" style="display:none">I loved this book! I can honestly say I had never read a Steampunk novel before, however, I am interested in Steampunk as a concept so this book was a fascinating thought to me. I appreciated the depth behind each character. Everyone had a back story, and "skeletons in their closet" so to speak, that gave them the little nuances that built them into very intriguing characters. I could feel myself sympathizing with the entire cast of characters; not just the protagonists, but the villain as well. This was definitely a book that I didn't want to put down. Several nights, when I was beaten by sleep, I was found asleep with the book sprawled across my face and my glasses askew. This book is quite action packed and well worth the read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4343953362480335185" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
