        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2561110037" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14765241163708082674">(Not entirely sure f I mentioned &quot;spoilers&quot;, but be cautious if reading this, I do mention a few things)<br/><br/><br/>I enjoyed this book, and I loved the concept that everyone is aware of their time in life through a watch they have. But I think the only thing that really bugged be about this (and maybe I completely missed it, so comment if I did) was that it didn&apos;t say HOW people got their watches. Yes, it mentioned that some people were presented with their watches when they celebrated a certain birthday, </span>
  <span id="freeText14765241163708082674" style="display:none">(Not entirely sure f I mentioned "spoilers", but be cautious if reading this, I do mention a few things)<br /><br /><br />I enjoyed this book, and I loved the concept that everyone is aware of their time in life through a watch they have. But I think the only thing that really bugged be about this (and maybe I completely missed it, so comment if I did) was that it didn't say HOW people got their watches. Yes, it mentioned that some people were presented with their watches when they celebrated a certain birthday, but where do these watches come from? Who is deciding how much time everyone gets to live? What in the world caused everyone to start having these watches and know that if those broke their life ended and vice versa?</span>
  <a data-text-id="14765241163708082674" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


